The paper proposes a neuroevolution method for optimizing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for embedded systems, which falls under the category of neural networks and evolutionary computation (cs.NE). The focus of the paper is on image classification, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV). The optimization is done with respect to classification error and CNN complexity, which are both topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions reducing power consumption, which is a concern in embedded systems and falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
